    {
      "id": "imperative",
      "icon": "📣",
      "title": "Imperative",
      "subtitle": "L-Imperattiv — giving commands and instructions",
      "intro": "The imperative is used to give a command, request, warning or piece of advice. It has two forms: singular (you) and plural (you all).",
      "facts": [
        "Singular form is for one person: oħroġ, ikteb, poġġi, ipprintja.",
        "Plural form is for several people: oħorġu, iktbu, poġġu, ipprintjaw.",
        "Tip: drop the first letter of the present-tense verb to find the imperative. Example: nifhem (I understand) → ifhem (you understand!)."
      ],
      "items": [
        {"singular": "Imxi", "plural": "Imxu", "en": "Walk"},
        {"singular": "Ikser", "plural": "Iksru", "en": "Break / Turn"},
        {"singular": "Dur", "plural": "Duru", "en": "Turn"},
        {"singular": "Poġġi", "plural": "Poġġu", "en": "Sit / Put"},
        {"singular": "Ibgħat", "plural": "Ibagħtu", "en": "Send"},
        {"singular": "Ikteb", "plural": "Iktbu", "en": "Write"},
        {"singular": "Mur", "plural": "Morru", "en": "Go"},
        {"singular": "Aħraq", "plural": "Aħarqu", "en": "Burn"},
        {"singular": "Ersaq", "plural": "Ersqu", "en": "Move closer"},
        {"singular": "Eħles", "plural": "Eħilsu", "en": "Free / Get rid of"},
        {"singular": "Aħtaf", "plural": "Aħtfu", "en": "Seize / Snatch"},
        {"singular": "Irkeb", "plural": "Irkbu", "en": "Ride"},
